Data Cleaning and Feature 
Engineering
• Fixed headers and numeric types
• Dropped ID and cleaned education
• Renamed target to default
Feature Engineering:
● pay_trend – Overall repayment improving or worsening over time
● recent_vs_past_pay – Sudden recent delays compared to past 
behavior
● payment_variability – Month-to-month instability in payments
● delay_acceleration – Speed at which repayment delays are worsening
● longest_pay_delay_streak – Longest consecutive months with delayed 
payments
nsight: These features capture repayment behavior, trends, and risk patterns, 
making the model more effective at predicting defaults.
Target Distribution
•78% No Default
•22% Default
•Imbalance affects model learning
Credit Default Insights: Gender
•Male clients: 2,873 of 11,888 defaulted - 24%
• Female clients: 3,763 of 18,112 defaulted - 21%
Credit Default Insights: Education & Marital Status
•Graduate School: Lowest default rates (Singles 18%, 
Married 21%)
• University: Moderate risk (Married 24%, Others 27%)
• High School: Highest risk (Married/Others ~26%)
• Trend: Married clients tend to default more than singles 
across all education levels
•Others Education: Low default, but very few records -  
interpret cautiously
• Key Insight: Lower education + married status - higher 
risk; Higher education + single - lower risk
