Deep Learning Model with Class Weights - Architecture & Training Behavior
MODEL 
● Dense(64) → Dense(32) → Output
● Dataset imbalance: 78% non-default, 22% 
default
● Class weights: Non-default = 0.64, Default = 
2.25
● Focuses on correctly identifying risky 
customers
 Performance Impact – Class Weights
● Recall improved: 0.32 → 0.62
● False Negatives reduced: 677 → 378
● F1-score increased: 0.44 → 0.53
● Result: Much better detection of 
defaulters
Tuned Deep Learning Model — Architecture & Performance (Threshold = 0.50)
Tuned FCNN Architecture
● Dense 256 → BatchNorm → Dropout
● Dense 128 → BatchNorm → Dropout
● Dense 64 → Dropout
● Output Layer: Sigmoid activation
● Regularization: Batch Normalization & Dropout to reduce 
overfitting
Tuned Model Performance 
● Precision: 0.50
● Recall: 0.60
